{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c470f635-7304-402b-87b1-12fd9f02e2b5","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\nAfter updating, install the .NET 11 SDK, then run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking changes in APIs you use.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92979d68-6094-4473-98b7-d5618df6b787","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide concise instructions.","outputTokens":293},"id":"b24a93a6-48f3-45fb-a79a-f7ea361fcbd9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:51.236Z","parentId":"caf3e3e8-0db7-4051-950d-c7e09a944080"}
